  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "In *Game of Thrones*, the process by which the Night King transforms children into White Walkers is somewhat ambiguous, but it appears that the children do not immediately grow into fully adult White Walkers. Instead, the transformation seems to involve turning them into creatures of the same nature as the White Walkers, but their physical growth is not explicitly shown to accelerate.\n\nIn the episode **\"Oathbreaker\"** (Season 6, Episode 3), we see a flashback where the Night King transforms a human infant into a White Walker by touching it. The baby's eyes turn blue, indicating the transformation, but there is no indication that the child rapidly ages into an adult. Instead, it appears that the child becomes a White Walker in its infant form.\n\nThe White Walkers are ancient, otherworldly beings, and their exact nature and growth process are left largely to the audience's interpretation. However, the transformation seems to involve bestowing the essence of the White Walkers rather than altering the physical growth rate of the individual. This is consistent with the show's portrayal of the White Walkers as mysterious and largely beyond human understanding.",
